{
  "stem": "1965.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My brother Sammy and two other boys were sent to a Catholic priest home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There they lived with this priest for over six months.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After that, they came back to Wezembeek.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this is where Sammy stayed till the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I want to indicate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He told me that when he was in Wezembeek, one of the things that he remembers so well are two things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "One, in the courtyard, they used to strategically place mattresses-- not one after the other, but in different areas-- so that if anything should come from the sky, the children could run under the mattresses.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The other thing he remembered was-- and he said that devastated him-- when a German pointed a rifle when he was standing at the window, right to the window where he was standing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That devastated him terribly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Whereas my brother, Jacky, he was sent-- and I believe to Linkebeek.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But in his case, he never stayed in one place like Sammy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Sammy was in two places-- the Catholic priest for six months, a little over that, and all the time in Wezembeek.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But Jacky told me that he was every few weeks in another place, and many times had to spend his life in the forest-- in the bushes-- and just pick something from the earth to survive.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So his life was extremely traumatic for a three, four-year-old to-- running.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We who were six and seven, we were considered the oldest ones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we had to take care of the three and four-year-old ones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So we were already so old.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We did not know our childhood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We never had one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And so he somehow survived this constant shuffling from one place to another.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It was almost every few weeks he was moved around.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
